cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer vision tasks, specifically video object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel statistical approach to CNNs, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video processing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
